            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "hqXZL",
              "name": "cardBody",
              "fill": "$white-70",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "You've tried fixing this. \"Write in a professional but conversational tone.\" \"My audience is founders.\" \"Make it engaging.\" The output gets marginally better. Then you're back rewriting the hook, cutting corporate filler, adding your personality. Twenty minutes later, you wonder why you used AI at all.\n\nHere's what's actually happening: Claude trained on billions of web pages. Most web writing is middle-of-the-road. Professional. Forgettable. Optimized for search engines, not humans.\n\nWhen you ask Claude to write a LinkedIn post, it predicts what words typically follow other words. Those words are not yours. They're the statistical average of the internet.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Lora",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
